{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"575","heading":"Regional emergency communications coordination","label":"575 Regional emergency communications coordination","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s575","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/ch1/schXIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs575","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationAnother was renumbered section 1905 and was classified to , prior to repeal by , , .section 1805 of Pub. L. 107–296section 595 of this titlePub. L. 115–387, § 2(a)(4)132 Stat. 5163Dec. 21, 2018","Amendments2018—Subsec. (d)(2). substituted “Assistant Director for Emergency Communications” for “Director for Emergency Communications”.Pub. L. 115–278","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Change of NameReference to the Assistant Director for Emergency Communications deemed to be a reference to the Executive Assistant Director for Emergency Communications, see , enacted .section 571(g) of this titleJan. 1, 2021"],"amendments":["CodificationAnother was renumbered section 1905 and was classified to , prior to repeal by , , .section 1805 of Pub. L. 107–296section 595 of this titlePub. L. 115–387, § 2(a)(4)132 Stat. 5163Dec. 21, 2018","Amendments2018—Subsec. (d)(2). substituted “Assistant Director for Emergency Communications” for “Director for Emergency Communications”.Pub. L. 115–278"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"In general","label":"a In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s575/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s575","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs575%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"There is established in each Regional Office a Regional Emergency Communications Coordination Working Group (in this section referred to as an “RECC Working Group”). Each RECC Working Group shall report to the relevant Regional Administrator and coordinate its activities with the relevant Regional Advisory Council.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Membership","label":"b Membership","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s575/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s575","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs575%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Non-Federal","label":"1 Non-Federal","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s575/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s575/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs575%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s575/b/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s575/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs575%2Fb%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"State officials.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s575/b/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s575/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs575%2Fb%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Local government officials, including sheriffs.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t6/s575/b/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t6/s575/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft6%2Fs575%2Fb%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"State police departments.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"typ